item.title: Logo type thangg [GIMP]
item.dc:creator: @TimberWolves TimberWolves
item.description:
@TimberWolves wrote:

For GIMP, it’s meh. If you want to expand your skills, I recommend Photoshop. Anyways, back to your logo. The drop shadow looks ugly due to the rough edges on the text, and the opacity of the texture over the text needs to be turned down.

Also, call it graphics. GFX sounds nub-ish.

Its pretty bad, no lie. I mean its not even remotely good, its hard to tell what it is suppose to be.

South Haizcap East?

SouthEast Haiz cap?

What the hell are you talking about?
[/quote]I am talking about how its hard to tell what the hell it is suppose to be, it looks horrible. You need to work on your layout of your letters.

Most logos like that you would read the big stuff first.

S E - Which would be South East

After that you read top to bottom

Haiz - cap

Understand now?

Even more so if it was suppose to be “Shaize” The way you have the text it would be “SHaizE”. Which is completely idiotic.[/quote]
